gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 141, Thunder 139
gameRecap.excerpt: Stephen Curry gets the finger roll layup to fall with 0.2 seconds remaining in regulation to lift the Warriors over the Thunder, 141-139. Curry recorded 30 points (5-10 3PM), eight rebounds and seven assists for the Warriors, while Dario Saric added 20 points (4-7 3PM) in the victory. Luguentz Dort tallied 29 points (6-6 3PM) and five rebounds for the Thunder in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 1-0 in West Group C play; 5-1 in the regular season, while the Thunder fall to 0-1 in West Group C play; 3-3 in the regular season.
